## isochron Details (created 2026-03-13)

**Target:** `isodate` (gweis/isodate) — Python ISO 8601 date/time/duration parser
- 129M downloads/month, 174 stars, 61 forks
- Single maintainer (Gerhard Weis), sporadic maintenance (2.5-year gap Mar 2022 → Oct 2024)
- 28 open issues: duration parsing bugs (#95-97), time parsing (#87, #90), missing py.typed in builds (#94), no strict typing (#101)
- BSD-3-Clause license

**Package name:** `isochron` (verified available on PyPI)
**Python:** >= 3.10, zero dependencies

**Key differentiators:**
- Fixes all known isodate bugs (#85-101)
- Full type annotations — mypy/pyright strict clean, working py.typed
- Interval and recurring interval support (new, isodate lacks this)
- Immutable Duration class with proper total_seconds() (raises ValueError on non-fixed instead of silent 0)
- Drop-in isodate compatibility shim

**4 phases:** Core Parsing → Formatting/Intervals → Quality/Compat → Docs/Release
**QA task #339** in progress (priority 5).
**Journal entries:** #517 (research), #518 (decision).

